From 6e5cb88a9786e13849339c3d778d60d552e3b59d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 23:17:41 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 8/9] libavfilter: add libvmaf_tune filter (vmaf-tune helper)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

New 2-input video filter that runs alongside a 1-pass encode and emits
a recommended CRF for the next pass:

    ffmpeg -i in.mp4 -i ref.mp4 -lavfi '[0:v][1:v]libvmaf_tune' -f null -
    [Parsed_libvmaf_tune_0 @ 0x...] recommended_crf=23 (target_vmaf=95.0, observed_vmaf=96.40, n_frames=240)

AVOptions: model, feature, n_threads, recommend_target_vmaf (95),
recommend_crf_min (18), recommend_crf_max (51), recommend_passes (1).

Full impl per ADR-0312 (sub-decision retired):
  * Filter mirrors `vf_libvmaf.c`'s framesync `do_vmaf` pipeline:
    `vmaf_init` + `vmaf_model_load` + `vmaf_use_features_from_model`
    in init(); per-frame `vmaf_picture_alloc` + memcpy from AVFrame +
    `vmaf_read_pictures(ref, dist, idx)`; flush + `vmaf_score_pooled`
    (mean) at uninit().
  * The recommended CRF is a piece-wise linear mapping from observed
    VMAF onto [crf_min, crf_max] anchored at the per-PR's calibrated
    table (see uninit() comment); per-clip Optuna TPE search stays in
    `tools/vmaf-tune/src/vmaftune/recommend.py`.

ADR: docs/adr/0312-ffmpeg-patches-vmaf-tune-integration.md
